body:
Changes: * Option `--escape-bedrock` is removed. The function is always enabled now. Features: * Support for Haiku is greatly improved (Haiku) * CPU, GPU, Disk, Sound, Terminal, Terminal Font, Init System, Battery, Mouse, Keyboard, NetIO, CPU Usage, Physical Disk and OpenGL should work on Haiku now * SMBIOS related modules (Host, Bios, Board, Chassis, Physical Memory) should work in platforms with legacy BIOS system. * Support for Gamepad and Bluetooth are WIP. * Some bugs are found and fixed. * Remove `python-requests` dependency in `scripts/gen-*.py`. * Add cmake option `-DENABLE_EMBEDDED_AMDGPUIDS=BOOL` (disabled by default) * If enabled, fastfetch will embed the newest [`amdgpu.ids`](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/drm/-/blob/main/data/amdgpu.ids?ref_type=heads) file into fastfetch binary. * Weather module now honors `display.temp.unit` option (#1560, Weather) * Support Physical Memory module in NetBSD (PhysicalMemory, NetBSD) * Requires root permission * Improve non-intel CPU detection in NetBSD (#1573, CPU, NetBSD) Bugfixes: * Fix building in macOS 10.13 (GPU, macOS) * Properly round percent values when detecting volume (#1558, Sound) * Fix Physical Memory module doesn't work in `--format json` mode * Add some missing variable inits (GPU, Linux) * Fix `--localip-default-route-only false` not working with `--gen-config` (#1570, LocalIP) Logo: * Update Rosa linux * Add Haiku2 ---
